              <h2>Treatment</h2>
              <b>  LIFESTYLE CHANGES</b><br>
Obesity is mainly resulting from defects in dietary habits and sedentary lifestyle. To reduce excess weight and maintain it in normal range requires change in diet as well as lifestyle. It is difficult to change lifestyle and dietary habits, but support from family and friends along with good will power can make the difference.
When dieting, your main goal should be to learn new, healthy ways of eating and make them a part of your daily routine.
<br><br>
<b>Healthy diet-</b> following daily routine of healthy, nutritious and low calorie foods can help to reduce excess weight. A dietician can guide properly to choose healthy substitutes to previous unhealthy foodstuffs. Eating small quantity of healthy meals at regular intervals are always beneficial than heavy meals.
Regular healthy diet can provide results in few months depending upon obesity. But one should not skip meals or follow crash diet to lose weight as it is deficient in important vitamins and nutrients. This can lead to other health disorders.
<br><br>
<b>Regular exercise-</b> daily at least 30 minutes of regular exercise like walking, jogging, aerobics, etc. can help to shed off excess weight and maintain fitness of body. Those with orthopedic diseases can seek help of physician to provide alternatives to active exercises.
<br><br>
<b>Stress management-</b> yoga, deep breathing exercises, meditation can help to relieve stress.
<br><br>
<b>MEDICATIONS</b><br>
Medications for weight loss are only an extra option along with diet, exercise & lifestyle modification and not the only option. One may get carried away with this easier method to lose extra weight but it does not always help.
It is helpful only when diet and exercise are not sufficient enough for weight loss or patients BMI is 30 or more. It can also be given to patients with BMI of 27 or more along with other disorders like hypertension or diabetes.
These medicines should be taken only after advice of physician and it would take some months to give results.
<br><br>
<b>SURGERY</b><br>
